<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: ">ADAM Financial Group was created to help parents and students afford a college education without getting buried under a mountain of debt or draining their retirement savings.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: ">ADAM Financial Group focuses on helping students, student-athletes and their parents create a plan to help them get into and afford the college of their choice.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>We strive to be an enhancement to the high school guidance office, focusing not on the academic side but instead on the financial aspect of going to college.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>Too often we&rsquo;ve seen students and parents get lost in the confusing maze of the financial aid system.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>Most parents are under-prepared for the cost of a college education for their students and rely too heavily on "the system" to help them send their children to college and end up paying too much for their education.&nbsp; The national average of almost 6 years to get a 4 yr degree can be financially devastating for many families to endure!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>&nbsp;In addition, the average student now leaves college not only with a degree, but with almost $20,000 of debt!</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: ">Our services include financial aid strategies, loan analysis, award qualification analysis, ACT/ SAT preparation and qualification enhancement. Using conservative and effective strategies, ADAM Financial Group looks to help families not only minimize the cost of college but also allow parents to continue to save for a comfortable retirement while maintaining their current standard of living.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: ">Jim Baudreau CCPS is the founder and President of ADAM Financial Group.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>He created this company in response to seeing too many clients struggle with trying to understand the complex financial aid system and suffer through the financial hardship of trying to pay for college.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>Since graduating college he has worked in the financial services field, and he holds a Series 7, 63 and 65 securities license as well as his NC LAH (life, accident and health) insurance license.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>Now he uses that experience and knowledge gained to make sure that families can maintain their standard of living, save for retirement, and still be able to afford a quality education for their children.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span></span></p>
<span style="font-family: "><span style="font-size: small;">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ">Jim is a graduate of the University of Tampa with a Bachelors Degree in marketing and finance.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>Jim played soccer at UT and reached the NCAA Div II Final four in his senior year.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>A lifelong soccer fan, Jim spent 10 years as a soccer referee.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>He is married, with 2 girls and lives in north Raleigh.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>He is a member of the National Association of Certified College Planners (NICCP) and holds the CCPS designation.</span></p>
